  "prompt": "How do I tune an acoustic guitar?",
  "response": "To tune an acoustic guitar, follow these steps:\n\n1. Use a tuner (electronic or smartphone app)\n- Digital tuners are the most accurate method\n\n2. Standard tuning from low to high (thickest to thinnest string):\nE - A - D - G - B - E\n\n3. Methods to tune:\na) Electronic tuner:\n- Pluck each string\n- Adjust tuning pegs until tuner shows correct note\n- Turn peg clockwise to raise pitch\n- Turn peg counterclockwise to lower pitch\n\nb) Tuning by ear:\n- Use a reference pitch (tuning fork, piano)\n- Tune each string relative to others\n- Use harmonics or comparison method\n\n4. Tuning steps:\n- Start with low E string\n- Tune each string one at a time\n- Make small, precise adjustments\n- Recheck strings as tuning one can affect others\n\n5. Alternative tunings:\n- Drop D\n- Open tunings\n- Alternate tunings\n\n6. Tips:\n- Tune regularly\n- Use new strings periodically\n- Be gentle when turning tuning pegs\n- Keep guitar in stable temperature/humidity",
